  to author a Word document.', 'latest', '# DOCX Editing & Generation Reference

## Overview

A .docx file is a ZIP archive containing XML files.

## Quick Reference

| Task | Approach |
|---|---|
| Read/analyze content | pandoc or unpack raw XML |
| Create new document | docx-js |
| Edit existing document | Unpack → edit XML → repack |

## Converting .doc to .docx

Legacy .doc files must be converted before editing.

```bash
python scripts/office/soffice.py --headless --convert-to docx document.doc
```

## Reading Content

### Extract Text

```bash
pandoc --track-changes=all document.docx -o output.md
```

### Access Raw XML

```bash
python scripts/office/unpack.py document.docx unpacked/
```

## Converting to Images

```bash
python scripts/office/soffice.py --headless --convert-to pdf document.docx
pdftoppm -jpeg -r 150 document.pdf page
```

## Accepting Tracked Changes

Requires LibreOffice.

```bash
python scripts/accept_changes.py input.docx output.docx
```

## Creating New Documents

Generate .docx files with JavaScript.

Install:

```bash
npm install -g docx
```

### Basic Setup

```javascript
const {
  Document,
  Packer,
  Paragraph,
  TextRun,
  Table,
  TableRow,
  TableCell,
  ImageRun,
  Header,
  Footer,
  AlignmentType,
  PageOrientation,
  LevelFormat,
  ExternalHyperlink,
  InternalHyperlink,
  Bookmark,
  FootnoteReferenceRun,
  PositionalTab,
  PositionalTabAlignment,
  PositionalTabRelativeTo,
  PositionalTabLeader,
  TabStopType,
  TabStopPosition,
  Column,
  SectionType,
  TableOfContents,
  HeadingLevel,
  BorderStyle,
  WidthType,
  ShadingType,
  VerticalAlign,
  PageNumber,
  PageBreak,
} = require("docx");

const doc = new Document({
  sections: [{ children: [] }],
});

Packer.toBuffer(doc).then((buffer) => {
  fs.writeFileSync("doc.docx", buffer);
});
```

### Validation

Always validate generated files.

```bash
python scripts/office/validate.py doc.docx
```

If validation fails:
1. Unpack
2. Fix XML
3. Repack

## Page Size

docx-js defaults to A4. Explicitly set page size for consistent rendering.

### US Letter

```javascript
sections: [{
  properties: {
    page: {
      size: {
        width: 12240,
        height: 15840,
      },
      margin: {
        top: 1440,
        right: 1440,
        bottom: 1440,
        left: 1440,
      },
    },
  },
  children: [],
}]
```

### Common Sizes

| Paper | Width | Height | Content Width |
|---|---|---|---|
| US Letter | 12240 | 15840 | 9360 |
| A4 | 11906 | 16838 | 9026 |

- Units are DXA
* 1440 DXA = 1 inch

### Landscape Orientation

Pass portrait dimensions and let docx-js swap internally.

```javascript
size: {
  width: 12240,
  height: 15840,
  orientation: PageOrientation.LANDSCAPE,
}
```

## Styles

Use Arial as the default font.

```javascript
const doc = new Document({
  styles: {
    default: {
      document: {
        run: {
          font: "Arial",
          size: 24,
        },
      },
    },

    paragraphStyles: [
      {
        id: "Heading1",
        name: "Heading 1",
        basedOn: "Normal",
        next: "Normal",
        quickFormat: true,

        run: {
          size: 32,
          bold: true,
          font: "Arial",
        },

        paragraph: {
          spacing: {
            before: 240,
            after: 240,
          },
          outlineLevel: 0,
        },
      },

      {
        id: "Heading2",
        name: "Heading 2",
        basedOn: "Normal",
        next: "Normal",
        quickFormat: true,

        run: {
          size: 28,
          bold: true,
          font: "Arial",
        },

        paragraph: {
          spacing: {
            before: 180,
            after: 180,
          },
          outlineLevel: 1,
        },
      },
    ],
  },
});
```

## Lists

Never manually insert Unicode bullets.

### Incorrect

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [new TextRun("• Item")],
});
```

### Correct

```javascript
const doc = new Document({
  numbering: {
    config: [
      {
        reference: "bullets",
        levels: [{
          level: 0,
          format: LevelFormat.BULLET,
          text: "•",
          alignment: AlignmentType.LEFT,
          style: {
            paragraph: {
              indent: {
                left: 720,
                hanging: 360,
              },
            },
          },
        }],
      },
    ],
  },
});
```

## Tables

### Critical Rules

* Always use WidthType.DXA
* Never use percentages
* Table width must equal the sum of column widths
* Set widths on:
    * table
    * columns
    * cells

### Example

```javascript
const border = {
  style: BorderStyle.SINGLE,
  size: 1,
  color: "CCCCCC",
};

const borders = {
  top: border,
  bottom: border,
  left: border,
  right: border,
};

new Table({
  width: {
    size: 9360,
    type: WidthType.DXA,
  },

  columnWidths: [4680, 4680],

  rows: [
    new TableRow({
      children: [
        new TableCell({
          borders,

          width: {
            size: 4680,
            type: WidthType.DXA,
          },

          shading: {
            fill: "D5E8F0",
            type: ShadingType.CLEAR,
          },

          margins: {
            top: 80,
            bottom: 80,
            left: 120,
            right: 120,
          },

          children: [
            new Paragraph("Cell"),
          ],
        }),
      ],
    }),
  ],
});
```

## Images

ImageRun requires a type.

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [
    new ImageRun({
      type: "png",
      data: fs.readFileSync("image.png"),

      transformation: {
        width: 200,
        height: 150,
      },

      altText: {
        title: "Title",
        description: "Description",
        name: "Name",
      },
    }),
  ],
});
```

## Page Breaks

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [new PageBreak()],
});
```

Or:

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  pageBreakBefore: true,
});
```

## Hyperlinks

### External Link

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [
    new ExternalHyperlink({
      children: [
        new TextRun({
          text: "Click here",
          style: "Hyperlink",
        }),
      ],

      link: "https://example.com",
    }),
  ],
});
```

### Internal Link

#### Bookmark

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  heading: HeadingLevel.HEADING_1,

  children: [
    new Bookmark({
      id: "chapter1",
      children: [new TextRun("Chapter 1")],
    }),
  ],
});
```

#### Link

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [
    new InternalHyperlink({
      children: [
        new TextRun({
          text: "See Chapter 1",
          style: "Hyperlink",
        }),
      ],

      anchor: "chapter1",
    }),
  ],
});
```

## Footnotes

```javascript
const doc = new Document({
  footnotes: {
    1: {
      children: [
        new Paragraph("Source: Annual Report 2024"),
      ],
    },
  },

  sections: [{
    children: [
      new Paragraph({
        children: [
          new TextRun("Revenue grew 15%"),
          new FootnoteReferenceRun(1),
        ],
      }),
    ],
  }],
});
```

## Tab Stops

### Right Alignment

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [
    new TextRun("Company Name"),
    new TextRun("\	January 2025"),
  ],

  tabStops: [{
    type: TabStopType.RIGHT,
    position: TabStopPosition.MAX,
  }],
});
```

### Dot Leader

```javascript
new Paragraph({
  children: [
    new TextRun("Introduction"),

    new TextRun({
      children: [
        new PositionalTab({
          alignment: PositionalTabAlignment.RIGHT,
          relativeTo: PositionalTabRelativeTo.MARGIN,
          leader: PositionalTabLeader.DOT,
        }),

        "3",
      ],
    }),
  ],
});
```

## Multi-Column Layouts

### Equal Width

```javascript
sections: [{
  properties: {
    column: {
      count: 2,
      space: 720,
      equalWidth: true,
      separate: true,
    },
  },
}]
```

### Custom Width

```javascript
sections: [{
  properties: {
    column: {
      equalWidth: false,

      children: [
        new Column({
          width: 5400,
          space: 720,
        }),

        new Column({
          width: 3240,
        }),
      ],
    },
  },
}]
```

## Table of Contents

Use HeadingLevel.

```javascript
new TableOfContents("Table of Contents", {
  hyperlink: true,
  headingStyleRange: "1-3",
});
```

## Headers & Footers

```javascript
sections: [{
  headers: {
    default: new Header({
      children: [
        new Paragraph("Header"),
      ],
    }),
  },

  footers: {
    default: new Footer({
      children: [
        new Paragraph({
          children: [
            new TextRun("Page "),
            new TextRun({
              children: [PageNumber.CURRENT],
            }),
          ],
        }),
      ],
    }),
  },
}]
```

## Critical Rules

### Document Structure

* Set page size explicitly
* Use separate Paragraph elements instead of \

* PageBreak must be inside a Paragraph

### Lists

* Never manually insert bullet characters
* Use numbering config with LevelFormat.BULLET

### Tables

* Always use WidthType.DXA
* Never use percentage widths
* Table width must equal column widths
* Cell widths must match columns
* Always set cell margins
* Use ShadingType.CLEAR

### Images

* Always specify image type

### TOC & Headings

* Use HeadingLevel
* Override built-in style IDs:
    * Heading1
    * Heading2
* Include outlineLevel

## Editing Existing Documents

### Workflow

1. Unpack
2. Edit XML
3. Repack

### Step 1 — Unpack

```bash
python scripts/office/unpack.py document.docx unpacked/
```

Features:
* Pretty-prints XML
* Merges adjacent runs
* Converts smart quotes to XML entities

### Step 2 — Edit XML

Edit files in:

```
unpacked/word/
```

#### Rules

* Use "Claude" as author unless specified otherwise
* Use direct edits instead of scripts
* Preserve formatting runs
* Use smart quotes

#### Smart Quote Entities

| Entity | Character |
|---|---|
| &#x2018; | '' |
| &#x2019; | '' |
| &#x201C; | " |
| &#x201D; | " |

Example:

```xml
<w:t>Here&#x2019;s a quote: &#x201C;Hello&#x201D;</w:t>
```

### Adding Comments

```bash
python scripts/comment.py unpacked/ 0 "Comment text"
```

Reply:

```bash
python scripts/comment.py unpacked/ 1 "Reply text" --parent 0
```

Custom author:

```bash
python scripts/comment.py unpacked/ 0 "Text" --author "Custom Author"
```

### Step 3 — Repack

```bash
python scripts/office/pack.py unpacked/ output.docx --original document.docx
```

## XML Reference

### Schema Rules

* <w:rPr> must appear last in <w:pPr>
* Use xml:space="preserve" when needed
* RSIDs must be 8-digit hex values

### Tracked Changes

#### Insertion

```xml
<w:ins w:id="1" w:author="Claude" w:date="2025-01-01T00:00:00Z">
  <w:r>
    <w:t>inserted text</w:t>
  </w:r>
</w:ins>
```

#### Deletion

```xml
<w:del w:id="2" w:author="Claude" w:date="2025-01-01T00:00:00Z">
  <w:r>
    <w:delText>deleted text</w:delText>
  </w:r>
</w:del>
```

### Minimal Edits

Only mark changed text.

```xml
<w:r><w:t>The term is </w:t></w:r>

<w:del w:id="1" w:author="Claude">
  <w:r><w:delText>30</w:delText></w:r>
</w:del>

<w:ins w:id="2" w:author="Claude">
  <w:r><w:t>60</w:t></w:r>
</w:ins>

<w:r><w:t> days.</w:t></w:r>
```

### Comments

commentRangeStart and commentRangeEnd must be siblings of w:r.

```xml
<w:commentRangeStart w:id="0"/>

<w:r>
  <w:t>text</w:t>
</w:r>

<w:commentRangeEnd w:id="0"/>

<w:r>
  <w:rPr>
    <w:rStyle w:val="CommentReference"/>
  </w:rPr>

  <w:commentReference w:id="0"/>
</w:r>
```

### Images in Raw XML

#### Add Media File

```
word/media/image1.png
```

#### Add Relationship

```xml
<Relationship
  Id="rId5"
  Type=".../image"
  Target="media/image1.png"/>
```

#### Add Content Type

```xml
<Default
  Extension="png"
  ContentType="image/png"/>
```

#### Reference in document.xml

```xml
<w:drawing>
  <wp:inline>
    <wp:extent cx="914400" cy="914400"/>

    <a:graphic>
      <a:graphicData uri=".../picture">
        <pic:pic>
          <pic:blipFill>
            <a:blip r:embed="rId5"/>
          </pic:blipFill>
        </pic:pic>
      </a:graphicData>
    </a:graphic>
  </wp:inline>
</w:drawing>
```

## Dependencies

* pandoc
* docx
* LibreOffice
* Poppler (pdftoppm)
