'', 3000, None, None, \"Cost of adding kid to Mom''s existing policy across 3 years (~$1K/yr young-driver surcharge).\")\n(None, None, None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''PATH 1: RENT YEAR 1 + WAYMO BREAKS, RE-DECIDE FUTURE SUMMERS'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''Item'', ''Cost'', None, None, None)\n(None, \"Summer 1 — Mom''s net rental cost\", \"=''Car Decision''!C22\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Year 1 vacations (Waymo)'', ''=C9*C10'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Summer 2 — expected (P × Year 1 rental)'', \"=C7*''Car Decision''!C22\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Year 2 vacations (Waymo)'', ''=C9*C10'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Summer 3 — internship, no transport'', \"=C8*''Car Decision''!C22\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Year 3 vacations (Waymo)'', ''=C9*C10'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Added-driver insurance (3 years)'', ''=C14'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''PATH 1 TOTAL — 3-year out-of-pocket'', ''=SUM(C18:C24)'', None, None, None)\n(None, None, None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''PATH 3: BUY ONCE, HOLD 3 YEARS (steel-man case for buying)'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''Item'', ''Cost'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Depreciation over 3 years'', ''=C6'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Sales tax (not recovered on resale)'', \"=''Car Decision''!C7*''Car Decision''!C10\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Title, registration first year'', \"=''Car Decision''!C11\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Registration renewals (years 2-3)'', ''=C11*2'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Insurance (36 months)'', \"=''Car Decision''!C14*36\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Repairs / maintenance (3 years)'', ''=C12*3'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Idle-car costs (3 years)'', ''=C13*3'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Opportunity cost on avg car value (3yr)'', \"=((''Car Decision''!C7+(''Car Decision''!C7-C6))/2)*''Car Decision''!C16*3\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''PATH 3 TOTAL'', ''=SUM(C29:C36)'', None, None, None)\n(None, None, None, None, None, None)\n(None, \"BOTTOM LINE — MOM''S 3-YEAR OUT-OF-POCKET\", None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''Path 1 — Rent year 1 + Waymo + flexibility'', ''=C25'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Path 3 — Buy and hold 3 years'', ''=C37'', None, None, None)\n(None, \"Mom''s savings with Path 1\", ''=C41-C40'', None, None, None)\n(None, None, None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''COST PER DAY OF ACTUAL TRANSPORTATION USE'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''Year 1 transport days (summer + vacations)'', \"=(''Car Decision''!C6*30)+C9\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Year 2 expected days (P × summer + vacations)'', \"=(C7*''Car Decision''!C6*30)+C9\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Year 3 expected days (P × summer + vacations)'', \"=(C8*''Car Decision''!C6*30)+C9\", None, None, None)\n(None, ''Total expected transport days needed (3 years)'', ''=SUM(C45:C47)'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Path 1 cost per day of actual use'', ''=C40/C48'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Path 3 cost per day of actual use'', ''=C41/C48'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Path 3 cost per day OWNED (not used)'', ''=C41/(36*30)'', None, None, None)\n(None, ''Utilization rate (use days / owned days)'', ''=C48/(36*30)'', None, None, None)\n(None, None, None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''KEY POINTS FOR MOM'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''• Path 3 is the BEST case for buying — clean buy, light use, strong resale, no transaction friction. It still loses.'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''• Utilization is ~22%. Mom would pay for 4.5 days of asset to get 1 day of driving. The other 3.5 days are waste.'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''• Insurance does not pause. Registration does not pause. Depreciation does not pause. The car does not care if you are home.'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''• Path 1 spends $0 on summer 3 because of internship. Path 3 keeps spending whether you are there or not.'', None, None, None, None)\n(None, \"• Waymo at $1,050/year covers every short trip. It is the entire ''but what about breaks'' problem solved cheaply.\", None, None, None, None)\n(None, ''• Path 1 preserves optionality: re-decide each summer based on actual plans, not a 3-year commitment made today.'', None, None, None, None)\n", "type": "text"}], "is_error": false, "tool_use_id": "sevt_01KKrnuYxuQbXuzkfvAwwZpj", "processed_at": "2026-05-10T01:00:44.189Z"}', '2026-05-10 01:00:44.189+00', '2026-05-10 01:00:47.063203+00'),
	('f701409e-6376-4984-a37c-22687d003771', '3eb76576-b597-4482-98cf-ec3310562774', 'sevt_01585oBnMaC21KECHRQbMk9X', 'span.model_request_start', '{"id": "sevt_01585oBnMaC21KECHRQbMk9X", "type": "span.model_request_start", "processed_at": "2026-05-10T01:00:44.305Z"}', '2026-05-10 01:00:44.305+00', '2026-05-10 01:00:47.063203+00'),
	('ec906100-1df4-4602-9f58-182bd8b2f396', '3eb76576-b597-4482-98cf-ec3310562774', 'sevt_01DkznHjwuHn9uu5ZD3SS1LD', 'agent.message', '{"id": "sevt_01DkznHjwuHn9uu5ZD3SS1LD", "type": "agent.message", "content": [{"text": "Ah, this is fresh-squeezed gold! 🍋 You''ve got a **comprehensive rent vs. buy decision analysis** for a summer car scenario. Here''s the juice:\n\n## **The Setup**\n- **Question:** Should your mom rent a car for the summer, or buy one and flip it?\n- **Key context:** 4-month summer, $22k car purchase price, $8k total rental cost\n\n## **Key Findings (Sheet 1: Car Decision)**\n\n**Option A (Rent):** Mom''s net cost = ~$5,000 (after your $750/month contribution)\n**Option B (Buy & Sell):** Mom''s cost = ~$4,100\n\n💡 **Close call!** But renting wins when you factor in real-world risks not in the numbers:\n- Major mechanical failures could blow the $600 repair reserve\n- Selling a car takes 5-6 months, not 4\n- All risk transfers to mom on ownership\n\n## **Sheet 2: 3-Year View** \nThe spreadsheet also stress-tests a longer horizon:\n- **Path 1 (Rent year 1 + Waymo for breaks):** More expensive upfront but keeps optionality\n- **Path 3 (Buy and hold 3 years):** Still loses financially because the car sits idle 78% of the time—insurance, registration, and depreciation don''t care if you''re home\n\n**Utilization is brutal:** Only ~22% of owned days actually get used. You''d be paying for 4.5 days of car ownership to get 1 day of driving.\n\n**The verdict:** Renting or Waymo-ing ($50/day for vacations) is the financially smarter move. Want me to tweak any assumptions or dive deeper into a specific scenario? 🧡", "type": "text"}], "processed_at": "2026-05-10T01:00:50.565Z"}', '2026-05-10 01:00:50.565+00', '2026-05-10 01:00:51.890444+00'),
