	('d01cef4f-349c-4f08-9f3f-973c85bed11d', '333f89ca-368e-4f1b-87b2-390fbf13c6b1', 'sevt_01Vpg5zSutBHpDKmSzxMrWWk', 'agent.message', '{"id": "sevt_01Vpg5zSutBHpDKmSzxMrWWk", "type": "agent.message", "content": [{"text": "📊 **Fresh-Squeezed Gold Price Update!** 🥇\n\nHere''s the juice on what''s happening with gold prices:\n\n", "type": "text"}, {"text": "The price of gold stood at $4,724 per ounce as of May 8, 2026", "type": "text"}, {"text": ". That''s some solid momentum! \n\n**Recent Trends:**\n- ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Gold opened at $4,702.20 per troy ounce on Thursday, the highest opening price since April 27", "type": "text"}, {"text": ", showing some nice upward pressure!\n- ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Gold prices rose in India on Friday", "type": "text"}, {"text": ", and the rally seems to be spreading globally.\n\n**What''s Driving the Gains:**\n", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Gold prices on the Multi-Commodity Exchange (MCX) rose, driven by a weaker dollar, a fall in oil prices, and clarity on a potential US-Iran peace deal", "type": "text"}, {"text": ". It''s like the market is blending together a bunch of positive factors! \n\n**The Market Juice:**\n", "type": "text"}, {"text": "When the Dollar depreciates, Gold tends to rise. Gold tends to rise with lower interest rates, while higher cost of money usually weighs down on the yellow metal", "type": "text"}, {"text": ".\n\nSo basically, gold is getting pressurized like we''re making Pressed juice right now—lots of external forces pushing it upward! 🍊💛", "type": "text"}], "processed_at": "2026-05-10T03:59:47.938Z"}', '2026-05-10 03:59:47.938+00', '2026-05-10 04:07:57.766692+00'),
