", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Global oil supply is expected to increase by 1.2 mb/d in 2025, while oil demand is expected to rise by only 0.7 mb/d, creating a supply surplus", "type": "text"}, {"text": ".\n\n### **Key Factors Influencing Prices**\n\n1. **Geopolitical Tensions**: ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "If Iranian oil supply dropped by a million barrels a day due to tighter sanctions, Brent could rise to the mid-$80s per barrel by mid-2025", "type": "text"}, {"text": ".\n\n2. **Production Dynamics**: ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Non-OPEC hydrocarbon liquids supply is expected to increase by 1.7 million barrels per day in 2025, with most growth coming from the US, Canada, Brazil, and Guyana", "type": "text"}, {"text": ".\n\n3. **Demand Concerns**: ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Oil consumption growth decelerated in China, Europe and Central Asia, and Latin America and the Caribbean, with electric vehicles accounting for more than 40 percent of new car sales in China in 2024", "type": "text"}, {"text": ".\n\nThe juice is definitely being *squeezed* from oil prices with that supply-demand imbalance! 🍊📉", "type": "text"}], "processed_at": "2026-05-10T05:23:16.613Z"}', '2026-05-10 05:23:16.613+00', '2026-05-10 05:24:24.583474+00'),
