	('13c7e8dd-a406-4b61-ad88-beea8b5f9c64', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01KnAVzuYhYuKAGAYQinNFGc', 'agent.message', '{"id": "sevt_01KnAVzuYhYuKAGAYQinNFGc", "type": "agent.message", "content": [{"text": "Your gerbils deck is ready at `/mnt/session/outputs/Gerbils.pptx` — 9 slides built directly on top of the FY26 Pressed Juicery template so it inherits the brand''s masters, fonts, and accent treatments.\n\n**Slide rundown**\n\n1. **Title** — black title slide with the Pressed wordmark and leaf monogram: *\"Gerbils — A Field Guide to Tiny Desert Explorers\"*\n2. **Contents** — four numbered chapters (Meet the Gerbil → Built for the Desert → Daily Life & Diet → Care at Home)\n3. **Meet the Gerbil** *(green accent)* — lead paragraph + taxonomy table on the left, four stat cards on the right (4 in, 1 oz, 3–4 yr, 40+ species)\n4. **Built for the Desert** *(yellow accent)* — four numbered adaptation columns: water-thrifty, long-tailed balance, powerful diggers, ever-growing teeth\n5. **Daily Life & Behavior** *(two-content)* — green \"Awake / Active\" panel vs. purple \"Resting / Burrowing\" panel\n6. **Diet & Nutrition** *(blue accent)* — proportional stacked bar showing 60% seeds, 20% pellets, 12% veg, 5% protein, 3% fruit, plus a feeding-notes list\n7. **Care at Home** *(purple accent)* — 2×3 grid of essentials (deep bedding, glass tank, companions, solid wheel, sand bath, quiet handling)\n8. **Did You Know?** — three green-bordered fun-fact cards (foot-thumping, fragile tails, lifelong pair bonds)\n9. **Thank You** — black end page matching slide 1\n\nThe file is large (~304 MB) because it carries the full template''s master/layout media — same as the source FY26 file. Open it in PowerPoint or Google Slides and everything is editable.", "type": "text"}], "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:07:55.746Z"}', '2026-05-10 21:07:55.746+00', '2026-05-10 21:08:22.720819+00'),
	('db97a94a-2b21-45a6-9b04-a85aa584ef87', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01LssFBB8wxoSQDE7GEEeiB2', 'span.model_request_end', '{"id": "sevt_01LssFBB8wxoSQDE7GEEeiB2", "type": "span.model_request_end", "is_error": false, "model_usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "output_tokens": 657, "cache_read_input_tokens": 81505, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 284}, "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:07:55.834Z", "model_request_start_id": "sevt_01ABo6dTdRsKxgT2zsYpVg88"}', '2026-05-10 21:07:55.834+00', '2026-05-10 21:08:22.720819+00'),
	('59291cbb-c58b-45b1-a0ee-678478661f52', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01RaYgf567Abwu8QtqV8BnkL', 'session.thread_status_idle', '{"id": "sevt_01RaYgf567Abwu8QtqV8BnkL", "type": "session.thread_status_idle", "agent_name": "Power Point", "stop_reason": {"type": "end_turn"}, "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:07:55.965Z", "session_thread_id": "sthr_018R8GKXE9mg9Zz6WvcKuYUa"}', '2026-05-10 21:07:55.965+00', '2026-05-10 21:08:22.720819+00'),
	('8be8b43b-3e41-48c5-9b5b-6ce8bf13dd75', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01Pjgenqd95h4Hz8Uq2JMEbC', 'session.status_idle', '{"id": "sevt_01Pjgenqd95h4Hz8Uq2JMEbC", "type": "session.status_idle", "stop_reason": {"type": "end_turn"}, "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:07:56.019Z"}', '2026-05-10 21:07:56.019+00', '2026-05-10 21:08:22.720819+00'),
	('85863742-f079-4f37-85ff-cd1edcd996f2', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01EAxCEKHzDXFo1hCfX9fiZo', 'user.message', '{"id": "sevt_01EAxCEKHzDXFo1hCfX9fiZo", "type": "user.message", "content": [{"text": "so that seemed to take a bit what was confusing abt your harness, what would u like to remember?", "type": "text"}]}', '2026-05-10 21:09:27.483+00', '2026-05-10 21:09:27.483978+00'),
	('c3ae95f5-a3f3-47f4-b29d-e822afee9e7d', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01EXdhKAnUmSeLwneunHa1M8', 'session.status_running', '{"id": "sevt_01EXdhKAnUmSeLwneunHa1M8", "type": "session.status_running", "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:09:26.766Z"}', '2026-05-10 21:09:26.766+00', '2026-05-10 21:09:33.217844+00'),
	('e6dde3ed-041d-4d20-b74f-701eebe26a46', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01YQX3TUKomSwKE4JgHj3sSz', 'session.thread_status_running', '{"id": "sevt_01YQX3TUKomSwKE4JgHj3sSz", "type": "session.thread_status_running", "agent_name": "Power Point", "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:09:26.766Z", "session_thread_id": "sthr_018R8GKXE9mg9Zz6WvcKuYUa"}', '2026-05-10 21:09:26.766+00', '2026-05-10 21:09:33.217844+00'),
	('e4e78ee0-b79f-409b-bd97-55ce31605b07', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01PyEcbmAkQGAA9rVTcD2wDj', 'span.model_request_start', '{"id": "sevt_01PyEcbmAkQGAA9rVTcD2wDj", "type": "span.model_request_start", "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:09:27Z"}', '2026-05-10 21:09:27+00', '2026-05-10 21:09:33.217844+00'),
	('163c2cfb-84cf-498a-951b-243c3f7ee2f8', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_01XDgBV19EqojNhZFJLnum3B', 'agent.message', '{"id": "sevt_01XDgBV19EqojNhZFJLnum3B", "type": "agent.message", "content": [{"text": "Good question. A few things tripped me up that would be worth remembering for next time:\n\n**Template discovery**\n- The \"FY26 Template\" wasn''t in `/mnt/session/uploads/` initially — it lives in the knowledge base. I had to call `kb_list` to find it and `kb_attach` to mount it. Worth checking the KB first whenever a user references a named file that isn''t in uploads.\n\n**Skill scripts that don''t exist**\n- The pptx SKILL.md references `scripts/thumbnail.py` and `scripts/office/unpack.py`, but `/workspace/skills/pptx/` only contains `SKILL.md` — no `scripts/` directory and no `editing.md` / `pptxgenjs.md` companions. I worked around it with `libreoffice --headless --convert-to pdf` + `pdftoppm` directly, which is fine, but the skill doc is misleading about what''s actually available.\n\n**Slide deletion in python-pptx**\n- The naive approach (`sldIdLst.remove(s)`) leaves orphaned slide parts in the package, which then collide on save with \"Duplicate name: ppt/slides/slideN.xml\" warnings and corrupt the output. The fix is to also drop the relationship (`prs.part.drop_rel(rid)`) **and** remove the part from `prs.part.package._parts`. This is non-obvious and cost me a render cycle. Worth caching as a known pattern.\n\n**Layout-baked decoration is invisible until you render**\n- The List Slide (layout 19) draws its three rounded card outlines directly on the layout itself, not via placeholders. Hiding the placeholders doesn''t remove the cards — they show through underneath anything you draw on top. The lesson: always render an empty test slide of any layout I plan to use *before* designing on top of it, so I know what''s baked in vs. what''s a placeholder.\n\n**Default placeholder text isn''t inherited**\n- The End Page 2 layout shows \"Thank You\" because the *original* slide had it set explicitly — the layout''s prompt text doesn''t carry into new slides made from that layout. Always explicitly set every visible string, even if it \"should\" be there.\n\n**Template size**\n- The 305 MB template means every render cycle (save → soffice → pdftoppm) is slow. For big templates, it''s worth doing one combined preview pass that renders multiple test layouts at once (which I did on the second try) rather than iterating slide-by-slide.\n\n**What I''d want preserved as a reusable note**\n1. The robust `delete_all_slides()` function (drop sldId + rel + package part).\n2. \"Render an empty layout before designing on it\" as a mandatory step when using an unfamiliar template.\n3. KB-first lookup when the user names a file not in uploads.\n4. The pptx skill scripts referenced in SKILL.md aren''t actually present in this environment — don''t rely on them.", "type": "text"}], "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:09:56.785Z"}', '2026-05-10 21:09:56.785+00', '2026-05-10 21:10:02.230507+00'),
	('0250ad17-2885-4aaa-bea0-98894b420a77', '7e900716-2bec-4758-a757-d1d0dd31b316', 'sevt_0176QLaQ9TaJCRSwJDTroPUt', 'span.model_request_end', '{"id": "sevt_0176QLaQ9TaJCRSwJDTroPUt", "type": "span.model_request_end", "is_error": false, "model_usage": {"input_tokens": 6, "output_tokens": 950, "cache_read_input_tokens": 8085, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 74391}, "processed_at": "2026-05-10T21:09:56.878Z", "model_request_start_id": "sevt_01PyEcbmAkQGAA9rVTcD2wDj"}', '2026-05-10 21:09:56.878+00', '2026-05-10 21:10:02.230507+00'),
